The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wednesday, July 16, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, July 16, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	AJC Bose Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-AJC Bose Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Film				 																																	Herbert Wises Julius Caesar will be screened, as part of Tragedies: A Festival of Shakespeare in film, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre at 6 pm.				 																Meet				 																																	Kautilya 03, a consulting event presented by IIM Calcutta, on the Joka campus, from 9.30 pm.				 																Pottery				 																																	An exhibition of teracotta, ceramics and studio pottery will be inaugurated by Mamata Shankar at Sasha at 11.30 am.				 																Festivity				 																																	Shravan Utsav, organised by Ban Bandhu Parishad, at Calcutta Ice Skating Rink.				 																Art watch				 																																	Prachi-Protichee, an art exhibition featuring artists of India and Bangladesh, will be unveiled at Chitrakoot Art Gallery at 6.30 pm.				 																																	Paintings and sculptures by Anupam Mistri, Dipankar Ghosh, Hillol Kumar Gupta, Sankar Thakur and others on display at Metropolitan Art Salon from 3 pm to 8 pm.
